                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>For this quotation from <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_844">Voltaire</rs>’s <hi rend="italics"><ref target="biblio.xml#lit_445">Candide</ref></hi>, <ref target="let568.xml#n-3">see letter 568, n. 3.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Van Gogh means that <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_647">Roulin</rs> had arranged for him to leave the hospital for a short while on 4 January. On that day Roulin wrote to Theo: ‘Monsieur the house doctor felt slightly anxious about letting him go out; I told him that I would be in charge of accompanying him and seeing that he returns to the hospital’ (FR b1068).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
